Q.1 <!DOCTYPE html> is it a tag of html? If not, what is it and why do we use it? write in 55 word


Ans - Yes, <!DOCTYPE html> is a declaration used in HTML to specify the document type. It is not a tag but a document type declaration. It informs the web browser about the version of HTML being used. It ensures that the web page is rendered correctly by the browser according to the specified HTML standard.


Q.2 Explain Semantic tags in html? And why do we need it?

Ans - Semantic tags in HTML are elements that convey meaning about the content they wrap. Examples include <header>, <nav>, <article>, <section>, and <footer>. They improve accessibility, search engine optimization, and code readability. Semantic tags help structure the page and provide context to assistive technologies and search engines.


Q.3 Differentiate between HTML Tags and Elements?

Ans - HTML tags are used to define the beginning and end of an element in HTML. Elements refer to the entire construct, including the opening and closing tags and the content within them.


