Q.6 What are some of the advantages of HTML5 over its previous versions?

Ans - 
Some advantages of HTML5 over its previous versions include native support for multimedia elements (audio, video), canvas for drawing graphics, improved form controls, enhanced semantics with new elements (header, nav, etc.), built-in geolocation support, offline storage capabilities, and better cross-platform compatibility with mobile devices.

Q.7 Create a simple Music player using html only

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Music Player</title>
  <style>

    body{
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }
    .player {
      margin-top: 100px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      padding: 10px;
      background-color: #f1f1f1;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      border-radius: 4px;
      width: 500px;
      justify-content: center;
    }
    
    .play-btn {
      background-color: #4CAF50;
      color: white;
      padding: 8px 16px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 4px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="player">
    <audio id="audio" controls src="à¤¤à¥‹à¤¹à¤°à¤¾_à¤¯à¤¾à¤¦_à¤®à¥‡à¤‚_à¤ªà¤¿à¤¬à¥Œ_à¤¸à¤¿à¤—à¤°à¥‡à¤Ÿ_à¤—à¥‡_-_Tohra_Yaad_Me_Pibau_Cigrate_-_Bansidhar_Chaudhary_-_JK_Yadav_Films(256k).mp3"></audio>
    <button id="playBtn" class="play-btn">Play</button>
  </div>
  
  <script>
    const audio = document.getElementById('audio');
    const playBtn = document.getElementById('playBtn');
    
    playBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      if (audio.paused) {
        audio.play();
        playBtn.textContent = 'Pause';
      } else {
        audio.pause();
        playBtn.textContent = 'Play';
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>

Q.8 What is the difference between <figure> tag and <img> tag?

Ans - The <figure> tag is used to encapsulate a self-contained content, such as an image, illustration, diagram, or code snippet, along with an optional caption specified using the <figcaption> tag. The <img> tag, on the other hand, is specifically used for embedding an image in the HTML document without any additional content or caption.

Q.9 Whatâ€™s the difference between html tag and attribute and give example of some global attributes?

The HTML tag represents an element in the HTML structure, such as <div> or <p>, which defines the type and purpose of the content. An attribute, on the other hand, provides additional information or modifies the behavior of an HTML tag. Global attributes like "class", "id", "style", and "title" can be used on various HTML tags to provide common functionalities and styling.










